        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1609216909" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14578159260890964738">This is a wonderful heartwarming story. It is perfect for a summer read.<br/>It is told in the present day and a story in a 1940’s diary. The stories are intertwined with one another.<br/><br/>Emily newly divorced is heartbroken is an author from New York City.<br/>She is given the opportunity to visit her aunt on Bainbridge Island in the state of Washington. The descriptions of the island are breathtaking, it makes you want to pick up and go there.<br/>Emily finds a diary in the bedroom in Aunt Bee’s home. Should she r</span>
  <span id="freeText14578159260890964738" style="display:none">This is a wonderful heartwarming story. It is perfect for a summer read.<br />It is told in the present day and a story in a 1940’s diary. The stories are intertwined with one another.<br /><br />Emily newly divorced is heartbroken is an author from New York City.<br />She is given the opportunity to visit her aunt on Bainbridge Island in the state of Washington. The descriptions of the island are breathtaking, it makes you want to pick up and go there.<br />Emily finds a diary in the bedroom in Aunt Bee’s home. Should she read it?<br />Well maybe just the first page. Emily can’t resist as she discovers secrets of the past. There are so many unanswered questions that Aunt Bee will not discuss.<br /><br />This book is very captivating and full of suspense. Will Emily solve the mystery of the 1940’s diary? Read to find out you will not be disappointed.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14578159260890964738" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


